text:
     Each training program shall, subject to the availability of funding: 
          1.     Meet high school credit and graduation requirements;
          2.     Provide paid internships;
          3.     Recruit participants from all neighborhoods and schools; and,
          4.     Provide tuition assistance for post-secondary education or training that leads to specific career opportunities.
(Added by Ord. 224-10, File No. 100043, App. 8/13/2010)
